==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arbor vitæ
<hw>Ar"bor vi"t⟦ae⟧</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[L., tree of
life.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An evergreen tree of the
cypress tribe, genus <gen>Thuja</gen>. The American species is the
<spn>Thuja occidentalis</spn>. It is commonly used as an ornamental
shrub around homes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The treelike disposition of the
gray and white nerve tissues in the cerebellum, as seen in a vertical
section.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arbuscle</ent>⟦br⟧
